## Overview

The Rust implementation (`ontrack-rs/`) is a performance-focused rewrite of OnTrack. It compiles to native binaries with no runtime dependencies and provides both a CLI and a desktop GUI.

## Workspace Structure

OnTrack-rs is a Cargo workspace with three crates:

```
ontrack-rs/
├── Cargo.toml            # Workspace root
├── ontrack-core/         # Shared library
│   └── src/
│       ├── lib.rs        # Module re-exports
│       ├── config.rs     # .env configuration
│       ├── parser.rs     # Address parsing
│       ├── geocoder.rs   # Geocoding (Nominatim/Google)
│       ├── matrix.rs     # Distance matrix
│       ├── solver.rs     # TSP solver (2-opt, NN)
│       └── exporter.rs   # Output generation
├── ontrack-cli/          # CLI binary
│   └── src/main.rs
└── ontrack-gui/          # GUI binary (egui)
    └── src/main.rs
```

## Key Technical Choices

| Choice | Rationale |
|--------|-----------|
| Rust edition 2021 | Stable, well-supported |
| tokio (full) | Async runtime for concurrent HTTP requests |
| reqwest + rustls-tls | HTTP client without OpenSSL dependency at runtime |
| serde + serde_json | Zero-copy JSON deserialization |
| anyhow + thiserror | Ergonomic error handling |
| clap (derive) | Type-safe CLI argument parsing |
| eframe/egui | Immediate-mode GPU-accelerated GUI |

## Version

Current version: **2.0.0** (defined in workspace `Cargo.toml`)

